": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "partridge"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, O, Msb;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaboj", "text_ar": "قَبْج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Lh, Mgh;) but ISd says, I know not whether Lh mean by this the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaA", "text_ar": "قَطَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "karawaAn", "text_ar": "كَرَوَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", nor do I know that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaboH", "text_ar": "قَبْح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the same as the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaA", "text_ar": "قَطَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sand-grouse"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaEaAqiybu", "text_ar": "يَعَاقِيبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, Mgh, O, Msb.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaA^an~akumo yaEaAqiybu AlHajali", "text_ar": "كَاَنَّكُمْ يَعَاقِيبُ الحَجَلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in a trad., means ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As though ye were the males of partridges"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] in your haste, and your flying into destruction: for they are such that, when they see the female in the possession of the fowler, they throw themselves upon him, so as to fall into his hand. (Z, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rkb", "text_ar": "ركب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b2-  And accord. to some, (TA,) the pl. also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Horses:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "they being thus termed as being likened to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yEAqyb", "text_ar": "يعاقيب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, TA,) because of their swiftness: (TA:) so in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakoDa", "text_ar": "رَكْضَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlyaEaAqiybi", "text_ar": "اليَعَاقِيبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As the running of the horses,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the swift horses"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; in a verse of Selámeh Ibn-Jendel: (O, TA:) but others say that the meaning [here] is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the males of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) It is said in the L that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "farasN yaEoquwbN", "text_ar": "فَرَسٌ يَعْقُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A horse that has a run after another run"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the power of repeating his running"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*uw EaqobK", "text_ar": "ذُو عَقْبٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqibK", "text_ar": "عَقِبٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]). (TA.) ―         -b3-  J has cited [in the S] the words of a poet,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "EaAlK yuqaS~iru duwnahu AlyaEoquwbu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "High,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so that"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yEqwb", "text_ar": "يعقوب"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "falls short of reaching it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] as an ex. of the last word meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but IB says that it appears to mean in this case"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuqaAb", "text_ar": "عُقَاب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eagle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alyaroxuwmu", "text_ar": "اليَرْخُومُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means the male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raxam", "text_ar": "رَخَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlyaHobuwru", "text_ar": "اليَحْبُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HubaAraY", "text_ar": "حُبَارَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hajal", "text_ar": "حَجَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is not known to have so high a flight: and ElFarezdak describes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaEaAqiyb", "text_ar": "يَعَاقِيب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as congregating with vultures over the slain. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["K", "TA", "O"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}